  "text": "Another interesting result to be shown here is the instantaneous error signal, j ε . Fig. 19 shows various cases for the sampled version of this signal after running the proposed model three times for three values of the learning speed μ . The results justify the mathematical proof in [CITATION_1] which is given by equation (9) and states that if μ is chosen to be 0.5, the output of the adaptive LMS spectrum analyzer will be equal to the DFT of the input sampled signal at the previous time instance. Otherwise, j ε will never reach zero as the case shows in Fig. 19 (a) . Fig. 19 (c) shows that when μ is chosen to be more than 1, j ε is increasing up to infinity as the LMS algorithm becomes unstable. ",
